    "body": "Also verified on Windows 7.\n\nYou need to put the `win.close()` statement after `win2 = new BrowserWindow...`.\nWhen running in `win.close()`, there is only one BrowserWindow win and electron will quit when the last BrowserWindow is closed. If we create a new BrowserWindow at quiting time, unexpected behavior will happen.  \n"
